Food Nutrition Facts Analysis

Xinting Gu, Yuchen Shi

USDA National Nutrient Database

  • This dataset contains 8790 foods and 51 nutrition profiles of those food.
  • We want to focus on the nutrition facts that people (especially people who workout or on diet) are familiar with and care about the most:
    • Energy(Kcal), Fat, Protein, Sugar, Carbohydrates, Fiber, Cholesterol, Sodium, Potassium, Vitamin A, Vitamin C, Calcium, Iron

Extract and Organize Data

We select the 13 nutrition facts we want to focus on and extract the category from food.

library(dplyr) category<-data.frame(do.call(rbind,strsplit(as.character(a$Shrt_Desc),“,”))) a$category <- category$X1 c<- a%>% select(Food=Shrt_Desc, category, Energ_Kcal, Protein_(g),Carbohydrt_(g), Fiber_TD_(g),Sugar_Tot_(g), Lipid_Tot_(g), Cholestrl_(mg),Sodium_(mg),Potassium_(mg), Vit_A_IU,Vit_C_(mg),Calcium_(mg),Iron_(mg))
